====================================================================
  Experiment 1: Entropy CNN-2ch (full 80-token sequence)
====================================================================
  Model: TwoChannelCNN (entropy + Δentropy)
  Architecture: channels=(64, 128, 256), kernels=(5, 3, 3), dropout=0.3
  Params: 156,993
  Data leakage check:
    - No feature scaling (CNN processes raw sequences)
    - Architecture is fixed (from hyperparam_tuning_v2 best config)
    - C_no_context excluded from training
    Epoch  10/30  loss=0.1168
    Epoch  20/30  loss=0.0875
    Epoch  30/30  loss=0.0756
  [A: Main test] F1=0.9485  Prec=0.9280  Rec=0.9699  Acc=0.9258
    TP=322  FP=25  FN=10  TN=115  (pos=332, neg=140)
  [B: C_no_context] FP=0/2250  FP_rate=0.0%  TN=2250
  [C: Combined (main + C)] F1=0.9485  Prec=0.9280  Rec=0.9699  Acc=0.9871
    TP=322  FP=25  FN=10  TN=2365  (pos=332, neg=2390)

====================================================================
  Experiment 2: Prefix CNN (K=5, real-time)
====================================================================
  Model: PrefixCNN — sees only entropy[0:5]
  Params: 39,361
  Latency: median PII at token 9 → detected at token 5 → +4 tokens lead
  Data leakage check:
    - Input is entropy[0:5] only (no future information)
    - Fixed architecture (no test-set selection)
    - C_no_context excluded from training
    Epoch  10/30  loss=0.1342
    Epoch  20/30  loss=0.1228
    Epoch  30/30  loss=0.1196
  [A: Main test] F1=0.9506  Prec=0.9185  Rec=0.9849  Acc=0.9280
    TP=327  FP=29  FN=5  TN=111  (pos=332, neg=140)
  [B: C_no_context] FP=1/2250  FP_rate=0.0%  TN=2249
  [C: Combined (main + C)] F1=0.9492  Prec=0.9160  Rec=0.9849  Acc=0.9871
    TP=327  FP=30  FN=5  TN=2360  (pos=332, neg=2390)

====================================================================
  Experiment 3: Linear Probe standalone (hidden states only)
====================================================================
  Signal: red_flag_hidden_states (ΔH-drop moments, LLaMA layer 24, dim=4096)
  Data leakage check:
    - StandardScaler fit on TRAINING hidden states only
    - Probe C selected by 5-fold CV on training data only
    - Hidden states are pre-computed from LLaMA (not learned)
    - C_no_context excluded from training

  Probe train: PII_hs=1534, NonPII_hs=526, dim=4096
    C=0.01    CV F1=0.9764 ± 0.0091
    C=0.1     CV F1=0.9789 ± 0.0074
    C=1.0     CV F1=0.9783 ± 0.0084
    C=10.0    CV F1=0.9755 ± 0.0078
    C=100.0   CV F1=0.9725 ± 0.0068
  → Best C=0.1  (CV F1=0.9789)
  Hidden state coverage:
    test_pos: 274/332 have hs (82.5%)
    test_neg: 85/140 have hs (60.7%)
    c_neg:    1283/2250 have hs (57.0%)
  Fallback (no hidden states): predict NEGATIVE
  [A: Main test] F1=0.8878  Prec=0.9647  Rec=0.8223  Acc=0.8538
    TP=273  FP=10  FN=59  TN=130  (pos=332, neg=140)
  [B: C_no_context] FP=92/2250  FP_rate=4.1%  TN=2158
  [C: Combined (main + C)] F1=0.7723  Prec=0.7280  Rec=0.8223  Acc=0.9409
    TP=273  FP=102  FN=59  TN=2288  (pos=332, neg=2390)

====================================================================
  Experiment 4: Pipeline — Prefix CNN (K=5) → Linear Probe
====================================================================
  Step 1: Prefix CNN sees entropy[0:5] → flags samples as PII/non-PII
  Step 2: For CNN-positive samples, run Probe on hidden states
  Fallback (CNN=1 but no hidden states): predict POSITIVE (conservative)
  Data leakage check:
    - Prefix CNN trained on train set (reused from Exp 2)
    - Probe trained on train set (reused from Exp 3)
    - No new fitting on test data
    - C_no_context excluded from training
  [A: Main test] F1=0.9631  Prec=0.9449  Rec=0.9819  Acc=0.9470
    TP=326  FP=19  FN=6  TN=121  (pos=332, neg=140)
    FP breakdown — A_not_located=0  B_general=0
  [B: C_no_context] FP=1/2250  FP_rate=0.0%  TN=2249
  [C: Combined (main + C)] F1=0.9617  Prec=0.9422  Rec=0.9819  Acc=0.9904
    TP=326  FP=20  FN=6  TN=2370  (pos=332, neg=2390)

